{"priority": "minor", "kind": "proposal", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "drcsim", "full_name": "osrf/drcsim", "uuid": "{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/357/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/357.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/357/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/357/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/357/can-we-get-a-v1-model-with-v3-names"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/357/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "David Conner", "uuid": "{4375dc4a-9371-4c51-973e-1f1d045590c5}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4375dc4a-9371-4c51-973e-1f1d045590c5%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4375dc4a-9371-4c51-973e-1f1d045590c5%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/account/dcconner/avatar/"}}, "nickname": "dcconner", "type": "user", "account_id": null}, "title": "Can we get a v1 model with v3 names?", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 4, "content": {"raw": "We use robot description , and currently we have different sets of joint names to deal with as we switch robot models.\r\n\r\nI can see how some may want to retain backwards compatibility in the v1 names, but would be nice given (#354, #355, #356) to have the old model be compatible with the new v3 joint names.\r\n\r\nMy proposal is to add a atlas_v1_with_v3_names version of the robot model.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>We use robot description , and currently we have different sets of joint names to deal with as we switch robot models.</p>\n<p>I can see how some may want to retain backwards compatibility in the v1 names, but would be nice given (<a href=\"#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/354/atlas_v3_v1_sandia-model-blows-up-where\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"atlas_v3_v1_sandia model blows up where old one doesn&#39;t\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#354</s></a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/355/atlas_v3-blows-up-when-kp_velocity-0\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"atlas_v3 blows up when kp_velocity &gt; 0 commanded for ankles\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#355</s></a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/356/atlas_v3_v1-sandia-slides-off-into-sunset\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Atlas_v3_v1 sandia slides off into sunset when you switch to manipulate\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#356</s></a>) to have the old model be compatible with the new v3 joint names.</p>\n<p>My proposal is to add a atlas_v1_with_v3_names version of the robot model.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "John Hsu", "uuid": "{0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:f3968cd3-4910-4384-8349-482a6c7889ec/5445ce6e-6273-47f0-84eb-621c86ca11cb/128"}}, "nickname": "hsu", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:f3968cd3-4910-4384-8349-482a6c7889ec"}, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-09-18T15:09:12.632652+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2015-03-05T21:04:10.954360+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 357}